import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sizes = data['size']
    n_bins = np.sqrt(len(sizes))
    n_bins = int(n_bins)

    plt.hist(sizes, bins=n_bins, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Size Distribution')
    plt.axvline(sizes.median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {sizes.median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['depth'], data['size'], c=data['depth'], cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Depth')
    ax.set_ylabel('Size')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the depth and the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Depth")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['num_children'] = data['children'].apply(lambda x: len(x) if x else 0)
    plt.hist(data['num_children'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Children')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of children for each node in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Extract the 'value' field from the dataset
    values = data['value']

    # Create a histogram of the 'value' field
    plt.hist(values, bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)

    # Add a vertical line for the median value
    median_value = np.median(values)
    plt.axvline(median_value, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {median_value:.2f}')

    # Set the title and labels
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the value of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

    # Add a legend
    plt.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Size')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the value and the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar(label='Group')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
